# Week 2 Results: Weather Surrogate Conformal Prediction

## Summary

Marginal conformal prediction with the supremum norm nonconformity score has been implemented and calibrated on held-out ERA5 data for the weather surrogate. We ran an in-distribution coverage check at the 90% and 95% nominal levels and compared results against a 5-member deep ensemble baseline.

## Experimental Setup

The weather surrogate is a small UNet trained on ERA5 reanalysis data from 2020 with 6-hour lead time prediction. Input is 4 channels covering geopotential and temperature at 500 and 850 hPa on a coarsened 90 by 180 grid. The dataset contains 363 pairs split 70/15/15 into 254 train, 54 calibration, and 55 test samples. Best validation loss was 0.00461.

